![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1578168281214-CZ1DG6DT1AHIY6BIK6O7/image-asset.jpeg?format=original)

Episode 50 is upon us! Instead of doing a normal review this week, we decided to dissect the characterization of Superman in 2013's Man of Steel, and decide what it's effects are, on the DCEU. While GT Rebirth is a devoted MOS defender, The Don feels it has more problems than it lets on. Watch these two battle passionately over the soul of the last son of Krypton, all the while trying to answer the question..."What happened to the Man of Tomorrow?"

If you can, please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the one stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
